column2: lots of bass this year- two swans
Found a dead trumpeter swan on North east side of the lake.
Saw three loons on the lake.  Big leaved pond weed coming to surfaces around deep hole (as seen so far).
Ice out 3/24/09- 20+ eagles feeding on the dead fish.
All of the previous years I would get a reading of 10' to 11' this year 3.75'.  Water is clear no algae but very yellow almost bronze.
Loon on east end of lake sunny 68 light breeze 10 mph
A little windy did not see any water fowl
no ducks- geese or loons Cool 60

Lake is a little high do to a lot of rain this spring
Tried to fishing again- but no bites- where are all the fish
lots of tannins in the water- from lots of rain- lake very high
The water is clear but very dark brown and the water level is very high- just below the top of the dock.
Lake is still very high- water clear but very brown. 70 light wind 5-10
A perfect day 67 no wind and sunny- a pair of swans and 6 of this years hatching swans.
little windy only a couple of coots on the lake.  Water is the highest I have seen for October.
One Loon on lake.  A little windy but not bad.  70 clear and sunny
